This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category as it proposes a distributed LSH scheme that reduces network cost and maintains load balance between different machines. It also involves large scale similarity search, which is a common application in distributed computing. 

It could also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category as LSH is a well-known algorithm for similarity search, and the paper proposes a new variant of it. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Databases (cs.DB) are also likely categories as LSH is commonly used in these fields for similarity search. 

Finally, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) is a less likely category, but it cannot be completely ruled out as the paper mentions experiments that verify the effectiveness of the proposed scheme in real-world applications, which could potentially involve machine learning or optimization tasks.
